Nirtzah – The Seder is Complete

We’ve made it. From slavery to freedom, from wine to more wine. We say together:
לְשָׁנָה הַבָּאָה בִּירוּשָׁלָיִם
L’shanah haba’ah b’Yerushalayim
Next year in Jerusalem — or at least somewhere beautiful, together.
We end this night full of story and sweetness, of salt water and hope. May we carry the lessons with us — and come back together next year, whole.
